  "change_summary": "Implements the Product-Owner-approved deck-change-design-v1.1: the three Urza's Tron lands are replaced by City of Brass, Mana Confluence, and Urza's Saga to improve colored access and artifact utility from the mana base, and Nevinyrral's Disk is replaced by Tezzeret the Seeker to trade the deck's only self-destructive board wipe for a proactive artifact tutor/untap engine. Land count stays at 34 and the Myr artifact-combo identity is preserved.",
  "expected_impacts": {
    "mana_fixing": "Colored sources rise from 21 to 23 and fixing lands from 12 to 14; the colorless-only Tron package and its incomplete-assembly failure mode are removed. New incremental painland life pressure is accepted and flagged for testing.",
    "artifact_engine": "Artifact tutoring rises from 7 toward 9 effective sources with direct-to-battlefield placement from Tezzeret the Seeker; his +1 reinforces the 6 untap engines and reuses the 14 mana rocks; Urza's Saga adds scaling Construct board presence from the land slot.",
    "risk_tradeoffs": "Board-wipe density drops from 3 to 2; the rare assembled-Tron burst ceiling is given up; Tezzeret the Seeker is a five-mana play on a 3.0-average curve; Urza's Saga self-sacrifices after chapter III, effectively lowering the land count by one over time."
  },
  "implementation_boundary": {
